        "subtopic": "First Pillar: The Legislature",
        "content": "• Responsible for making laws\n\n• Union Legislature is called Parliament (President + Rajya Sabha + Lok Sabha)\n\n• Rajya Sabha (Council of States): Upper house with members from states and UTs, Vice-President is ex-officio Chairman\n\n• Lok Sabha (House of People): 543 elected representatives, 530 from states, 13 from UTs\n\n• Earlier, 2 Anglo-Indian members were nominated (till 2020)"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Second Pillar: The Executive",
        "content": "• Responsible for implementation of laws\n\n• Includes Prime Minister, Union Cabinet, and Ministries\n\n• Ensures policies made by Legislature are translated into programs and services\n\n• Key role: Effective delivery of services to citizens"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Third Pillar: The Judiciary",
        "content": "• Interprets and applies laws\n\n• Protects Legislature and Executive from misuse of power\n\n• Ensures fundamental rights of citizens\n\n• Structure: Supreme Court (Apex), High Courts, and District Courts"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Fourth Pillar: The Media",
        "content": "• Acts as a bridge between government and people\n\n• Known as the Fourth Estate\n\n• Includes print, electronic, and digital media\n\n• Ensures transparency and accountability by publishing reports, agendas, and opinions\n\n• Upholds freedom of speech and expression"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Fifth Pillar: Emergence",
        "content": "• Focused on channeling people’s power against corruption\n\n• Includes NGOs, anti-corruption bodies, advisors, and special designations\n\n• Mission: Encourage, enable, and empower every citizen to eliminate corruption"
      },
      {
        "subtopic": "Key Features",
        "content": "• Every pillar must function independently while supporting one another\n\n• Strong democracy depends on resilience and balance among all pillars\n\n• Constitution acts as the rulebook for democracy\n\n• Federalism ensures power sharing between Union and State governments"
      }
