        "subtopic": "General Questions",
        "content": "• Q1. What is the main pillar of representative democracy? → Legislature\n\n• Q2. What are the four powerful pillars of democracy? → Legislature, Executive, Judiciary, Media\n\n• Q3. What is the central theme of democracy? → Equality, justice, and people’s participation\n\n• Q4. Why are these pillars important? → To ensure fair governance and prevent concentration of power\n\n• Q5. What role does the Constitution play? → Provides framework and protects rights of citizens\n\n• Q6. How does the Judiciary protect rights? → By striking down unconstitutional laws and safeguarding fundamental rights\n\n• Q7. What is Federalism? → Division of powers between Central and State governments\n\n• Q8. What is the Union Cabinet? → Group of ministers assisting the Prime Minister in governance\n\n• Q9. What is the relationship between Legislature and Executive? → Executive is chosen from Legislature, and Legislature monitors Executive’s functioning"
